gence\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3806}, {\"ngram\": \"their own nature\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their style is not an assumed manner, nor an imitation of a foreign perfection; it has grown from the inside and is an expression of the race and its history, and their weapons and finery are as much a part of their being as are a stag's antlers.\\\"\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 4200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their style\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 3964}, {\"ngram\": \"an assumed manner\", \"from\": 3972, \"to\": 3989}, {\"ngram\": \"an imitation\", \"from\": 3995, \"to\": 4007}, {\"ngram\": \"a foreign perfection\", \"from\": 4011, \"to\": 4031}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4061}, {\"ngram\": \"an expression\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4082}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 4086, \"to\": 4094}, {\"ngram\": \"its history\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4110}, {\"ngram\": \"their weapons\", \"from\": 4116, \"to\": 4129}, {\"ngram\": \"finery\", \"from\": 4134, \"to\": 4140}, {\"ngram\": \"as much a part\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4159}, {\"ngram\": \"a stag's antlers\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4198}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Maasai are a Kenyan and Tanzanian people.\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4230, \"end\": 4239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.275784701308294e-36, \"text\": \"Tanzanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tanzania\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Maasai\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because the \\\"anti-tribal\\\" Tanzanians do not include ethnicity in the population census, their population is estimated to be between 430,000 and 500,000.\", \"from\": 4248, \"to\": 4400, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the \\\"anti-tribal\\\" Tanzanians\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4284}, 